The paper deals with problems related to low-rank matrix completion and robust PCA, which are commonly studied in the machine learning and computer vision communities. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of algorithms and assumptions related to data structures and information theory, which suggests that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are also possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves numerical analysis and optimization, which suggests that cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possible sub-category as well.
